modules.description: Tracks metrics by updating counters, gauges, and timing data with specified sample rates. Operates on strings, integers, floats, and lists of strings to collect performance and operational statistics. Used to monitor system performance, track request rates, and measure execution times in real-time applications.

Tracks metrics such as timings and gauge values with customizable sampling rates, using strings and integers to represent metrics and their values. Updates statistical counters and adjusts values based on provided tags. Used for real-time performance monitoring and system health tracking in asynchronous applications.

Tracks metrics by sending UDP packets to a StatsD server, supporting increment, decrement, and gauge updates. Operates on integers, floats, and strings to represent counters, timers, and tags. Used to monitor application performance and system health in real-time.

Tracks metrics like counters, gauges, and timings using strings, integers, and floats, with support for sample rates and tags to refine data collection. It updates statistical values dynamically and aggregates performance data from real-time and asynchronous systems. Operations include incrementing counters, setting gauge values, and recording timing durations. Examples include tracking HTTP request rates, measuring response times, and monitoring memory usage with custom tags.
